data.description: Spent a week in Los Angeles with my friends and decided to visit the Last Bookstore as one of our stops. I came up with the idea of floating the book with help of my friend. data.description: Me and my sister were stuck at home one day, the sun had almost completely set but I still had that itch to get the camera out and start shooting. While racking my brain at what I could take photos of in the dark I remembered the sparklers I had laying around from bonfire night a few months back. I had come across a few sparkler photos in the past on Unsplash and with those in mind we shot this. Amazingly such a spur of the moment photo has turned out to be one of my most popular.
